ase 1 (Research):** Update description to emphasize external-only focus and one-pager output:\n```\nDiscover the agent's hook mechanism, transcript format, and configuration\nthrough binary probing and documentation research. Produces an implementation\none-pager at `cmd/entire/cli/agent/$AGENT_SLUG/AGENT.md` that the other\nphases use as their single source of agent-specific information.\n```\n\n**Phase 2 (Write Tests):** Update expected output to mention it uses the one-pager.\n\n**Phase 3 (Implement):** Already updated from previous commit. No further changes.\n\n**Gate:** Keep the INCOMPATIBLE gate after Phase 1.\n\n## What This Achieves\n\n| Before | After |\n|--------|-------|\n| Research reads all internal Entire docs | Research reads only `agent-guide.md`; implementer reads the rest |\n| Implementer re-reads internal docs | Same (but no duplication) |\n| Both phases may search external docs | Research does primary external search; other phases check one-pager first, fall back to external search, and update one-pager |\n| Research produces a report (consumed once) | Research produces a one-pager (consumed by both later phases) |\n| Test-writer asks user if no research | Test-writer reads one-pager directly |\n| Implementer has no record of external findings | One-pager persists as `AGENT.md` in the package |\n\n## AGENT.md Lifecycle\n\n- **Created** by research phase\n- **Read** by test-writer and implementer phases (their primary source of agent-specific info)\n- **Updated** during implementation if E2E failures reveal new information\n- **Committed** to the repo — serves as development documentation for future maintainers\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Read updated `researcher.md` — confirm no internal Entire doc reading, confirm one-pager output\n2. Read updated `test-writer.md` — confirm it references one-pager, confirm no external doc searching\n3. Read updated `implementer.md` — confirm it references one-pager for agent-specific info, confirm no external doc 